"Here's your medium-level Python coding question:\n\n{\"title\": \"Median of a Sorted Array\", \"description\": \"Given a sorted array, write a function that finds the median. If the length of the array is odd, the median is the middle element. If the length is even, the median is the average of the two middle elements.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef find_median(arr: list[int]) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `arr` (list[int]): A sorted array of integers.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the median of the input array.\\n\", \"code\": \"def find_median(arr: list[int]) -> int:\\n    n = len(arr)\\n    if n % 2 == 1:\\n        return arr[n // 2]\\n    else:\\n        return (arr[(n - 1) // 2] + arr[n // 2]) // 2\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert find_median([1, 3, 5, 7, 9]) == 5\", \"assert find_median([-1, -3, -5, -7, -9]) == -5\", \"assert find_median([1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9]) == 5\", \"assert find_median([]) == None\"]}"